race.comment: EDDYSTONE (1) is a Japanese recruit who ran a much-improved race at his first start for Andrew Bobbin, having previously been prepared by Henry Dwyer, when specked at long odds. Had clearly shown the new stable something before that and with the benefit of that run, and stepping up to 2000m, he can run an even better race. VAN ROY (2) beat EDDYSTONE home last start and while he wouldn't have the improvement of that rival, he's drawn to again be prominent throughout. MANGIONE (5) has struck a purple patch his past three and while the outside alley is a bit hit to his chances, he does get 1.5kg off through the claim and gets some weight off the top few. ADMIRE ACE (6) looked like he was going to drop out on the turn at Kilmore but motored late and while that was a weak maiden, he'll love the extra 400m.
